title: For Sale:  Rare sino soviet honor guard sks matching number
location: Chattanooga TN to Crossville Tn, Chattanooga, Tennessee
postcontent: I have a rare sino soviet sks that was an honor guard one. There were very few of these shipped over here before the ban. This is one of the rarest if not the rarest Chinise SKS that there is. The Sino Soviet Sks was made for 2 years and were assembled in China but was all Russian parts. These parts have the Russian star on them and this is a matching number sks which all original parts including the the cleaning kit. This is a good functional gun and still extremely nice. The honor guard rifles had the chrome looking parts on them for more looks and were starting to be shipped over here before the ban. This is a must for any gun collector. I am asking $800, not perfect cosmetically but still in great shape for its age. Works flawless.I could possibly interested in trades. I will trade for multiple guns. I do have more interested in pistols than long guns, but I could be interested in a Ruger 10/22 takedown for the right price trade in on this one. I could be interested in trades on ar or ak guns. I may ask for boot if I feel the trade is not equal but in the same sense I do not care to pay boot to equal out a trade if you offer me something that is worth more. I have several shells I could throw in to equal out trade or to swap out shells if someone trades an ar towards it.I prefer to keep my phone number private until I start communicating with someone with a gun or guns that I am interested in. If you make an offer, I will write you back instead of ignoring you because I remember what it is like to be on the other ending waiting for a reply to not get one. I check my emails multiple times a day.Thank you for your time and have a good day.

postcontent:
Beautiful rifle. This was a very difficult decision for me to make, as I am kind of in love with this rifle but am moving away from the larger calibers (such as, .308 and 7.62x54R). There have been exactly 0 failures or issues with it and I've put about 200ish rounds down range. Very accurate, especially with a good scope. I've a little obsessive-compulsive about cleaning, so rifle is very well maintained. Receiver, like all VEPR rifles, is from RPK design, so it's veritably built like a tank (and generally just tougher than other AKs).I installed a removable grip-wrap that makes the rifle featureless (so you can insert and detach magazines without using one of those Hellish contraptions they call an AK-bullet-button, yuck). title: For Sale/Trade:  2012 Wr450f
postcontent: 2012 Yamaha Wr450f- 870 miles, FMF Q4 exhaust, Cycra hand guards, Tusk dual sport kit (brake light, turn signals, etc).This bike was a left over from a dealership, it was first bought mid/late 2014. The original owner used it mainly for enduro riding and sold it to me around May 2015 because of financial issues. About a month after buying it I lost balance going up an incline and fell on my wrist wrong. I ended up breaking my scaphoid, so after that I didn't ride for a good 5 months.. Then winter came along.. So the bike pretty much sat for a year, id guess I've put around 6-8 hours on it. Despite barely ever being used the bike runs great, I go out and start it up every now and then and it starts up fine each time. Occasionally ill take it out for a quick spin around the block just to keep it warm. The tires still have good tread, the body plastics are slightly scraped up and the right front fender is chipped as you can see in the pictures. Also the left hand guard needs a new clamp/bracket (cheap), other than that theres just some minor scuffs here and there. The bike was rode for what it was meant for, if you want though it could easily be fixed up into a street beauty. The pictures show what looks like stains on the seat but thats just water, it also looks like there rust on the bottom but its just mud/clay. Im only selling it because id like a bike for the roads this summer and just don't have the money for 2 bikes.. Various other parts will be included. REMEMBER: The bank still has the title. The original owner is working on paying it off. I am the second owner. I have the bill of sale and still stay in contact with the original owner, he's a nice guy, this isnt shady at all. You will be able to speak to him yourself too. The bike has a clean vin and should be paid off by next year at the LATEST. If your looking for a bike just to keep out on the property or do some trail riding with or if you just don't care about a title then this would be a great buy! Its only priced so low because I know nobody wants to deal with this title situation. If you don't care though you'll save a couple thousand.. Give me a call or text and id be more than happy to go more in depth about everything. Thanks! -Caleb
